description: Pawan Kumar Chamling, the five-time former Chief Minister of Sikkim and leader of the Sikkim Democratic Front (SDF), faced a significant setback. He lost in both assembly constituencies he contested: Poklok Kamrang and Namcheybung. In the Poklok Kamrang seat, located in his home district of Namchi, Chamling was defeated by Bhoj Raj Rai of the Sikkim Krantikari Morcha (SKM) by a margin of 3,063 votes.
title: House run ends as five-time CM Chamling loses from both seats

description: Landslides often bring back painful memories for the people of Sikkim, but this term also perfectly captures the recent assembly election results in the state. Chief Minister Prem Singh Tamang’s Sikkim Krantikari Morcha (SKM) has secured a second consecutive term, clinching 31 out of 32 seats on Sunday. In contrast, the opposition Sikkim Democratic Front (SDF) managed to win only a single seat.
title: SKM bags 31 of 32, wins Gangtok on the trot; BJP, Cong draw a blank
RBI may keep rates unchanged
Brokers gear up to rein in market risks

description: Ten of the 11 MLAs who initially won the 2019 assembly elections under Congress and other parties' banners but later joined the BJP, achieved significant victories in the Arunachal Pradesh assembly polls. Opposition parties claim these MLAs switched sides due to "intimidation" from the BJP and to secure their positions. However, BJP in-charge for Arunachal Pradesh, Ashok Singhal, stated they joined the BJP voluntarily.
title: 10 of 11 turncoats who joined BJP post big wins in Arunachal polls
Most bank frauds are 3rd-party scams: IBA

description: Congress is struggling to find candidates for 41 out of the 60 assembly constituencies in Arunachal Pradesh, a state where it once dominated politics for over three decades. This decline is evident as the party now holds only one seat after another tough battle with the BJP. In 2019, Congress had secured four seats, but this time they could only contest 19 seats.
title: Congress’s woes: No contestants in 41 of 60 seats, a solitary win
Project woes: SOP likely for Chinese work visas

description: In January, a bronze statue of 'Jatayu'—the mythical vulture who fought bravely to save Sita from Ravana—was unveiled during the Ram Temple consecration in Ayodhya. At the same time, twenty real-life vultures, in urgent need of help, were gradually reintroduced into the vibrant Tadoba and Pench tiger reserves in Maharashtra.
title: Rewilding in tiger reserves helps near-extinct vultures soar again
Maruti calls for GST boost to hybrids

description: The Allahabad High Court has criticized the Enforcement Directorate (ED), the Serious Fraud Investigation Office (SFIO), and the Economic Offences Wing (EOW) for their inadequate investigation into the Shine City scam. In this case, several crores of investors' money were siphoned off by the accused parties. The court has fixed July 1 as the next date of hearing.
title: HC chides ED for 'shoddy probe' into Rs 1,000 crore Shine City scam

description: Just two days before the election results, which he expects will win him another five-year term, PM Narendra Modi had a busy Sunday. His schedule included presiding over seven meetings across various ministries to review preparations in response to the heat wave and readiness for the upcoming monsoon. Government sources revealed that PM Modi instructed officials to ensure regular drills for fire prevention.
title: PM Modi chairs review meets on heatwave, monsoon progress

description: The Election Commission on Sunday mandated a re-election at two polling stations in Bengal. One booth is in Deganga under the Barasat constituency, while the other is in Kakdwip under the Mathurapur constituency. The re-polling is scheduled to take place from 7 am to 6 pm on June 3. The decision was based on reports from poll officials, considering “all material circumstances on record.”
title: Repolling ordered in two West Bengal booths
Naveen Patnaik's stint as Odisha CM will continue, predict exit polls

description: A 30-year-old BJP worker was killed in Nadia. Women protesters freed a detained party worker from cops in Sandeshkhali. Accusations of attacks on party agents and workers have surfaced in Kolkata, reflecting a recurring pattern of post-poll violence in Bengal. In Nadia, Hafizul Sheikh was playing carrom in Kaliganj’s Chandghar area around 8pm on Saturday when 10-12 men arrived on bikes and opened fire.
title: BJP man killed in West Bengal post-poll violence, TMC denies role in it

description: The Election Commission (EC) has demanded Congress leader Jairam Ramesh provide evidence supporting his claim that Home Minister Amit Shah intimidated district magistrates (DMs) before vote counting. Ramesh alleged Shah had contacted 150 DMs to exert pressure. The EC, emphasizing the integrity of the counting process, requested details of the contacted DMs and the basis for Ramesh's claims by June 2.
title: After Jairam alleged Shah called DMs, EC says furnish details
India sends 90 tonne of API in aid to Cuba
Search on for Prajwal's mother, arrest soon: Karnataka home min

description: A 59-year-old convict in the 1993 Bombay serial blasts case was beaten to death on Sunday in Kolhapur's Kalamba Central Jail. Five inmates were involved in the assault. The prisoner, known as Munna, with aliases Mohammad Alikhan and Manojkumar Bhawarlal Gupta, was attacked near the prison’s bathing well. He was struck with concrete and metal covers of a drainage chamber at 7:55 am.
title: 1993 Bombay blasts convict beaten to death in Kolhapur jail
Porsche teen's parents' DNA test critical to prove blood swap: Cops

description: The Panvel City police apprehended a 30-year-old man from Haryana on Saturday. This arrest is linked to the recent shooting incident at actor Salman Khan's Bandra residence, allegedly involving members of the Lawrence Bishnoi gang. Senior inspector Nitin Thakare stated that Deepak Hawasingh Gogalia, also known as Jhony Valmiki, was responsible for arranging accommodation for the two shooters in Panvel.
title: Man held over Salman house firing, 7th to be arrested so far

description: Exit polls suggesting a likely third term for PM Narendra Modi and his BJP-led NDA have been met with skepticism by opposition leaders from the INDIA bloc. Former Congress president Rahul Gandhi and current chief Mallikarjun Kharge claimed the polls were manipulated to favor Modi and BJP. Gandhi dubbed them "Modi media polls" and confidently predicted a win for the INDIA bloc.
title: 'Rigged': INDIA bloc leaders trash exit polls

description: The ruling YSRCP has approached the Supreme Court to challenge a high court order. The high court had directed them to use an election petition to address concerns about the validity of postal ballots. YSRCP contends that the high court made its decision without evaluating the merits of their petition.
title: YSRCP moves Supreme Court on postal ballots

description: The nationwide toll of suspected heatstroke deaths surpassed 200, with 211 reported cases, 141 of which were in Odisha. Odisha reported 45 new deaths in the last 24 hours, with 26 confirmed as heatstroke, 8 attributed to other causes, and 107 under investigation. The worst-hit areas in Odisha include Sundargarh with 35 suspected deaths, Balangir with 20, and Sambalpur with 18.
title: Odisha reports 45 more heatstroke deaths in 24 hrs; India toll at 211

description: On Sunday, a delegation of INDIA bloc functionaries visited the Election Commission. They were there to discuss measures ensuring fair play ahead of the Lok Sabha vote counting set for Tuesday. The delegation requested that postal ballots, which can significantly influence poll results, be counted first. They also proposed that the results of these postal ballots be declared before the completion of EVM vote counting.
title: Must count postal votes first, says INDIA bloc

description: A delegation from the BJP, headed by finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman, met with the Election Commission on Sunday. They requested the EC to ensure a smooth counting process on Tuesday and to take action against those making "systematic attempts" to undermine the electoral process. The BJP also highlighted that opposition parties have been targeting the media.
title: BJP goes to Election Commission, claims bid to undermine poll
After wildfires, rain brings relief in parts of Uttarakhand

description: A Vistara flight from Paris, carrying 306 passengers, experienced a bomb scare that prompted an emergency landing at Mumbai airport on Sunday. This marked the third bomb scare in the country within a week and the second such incident in Mumbai over two days. Vistara reported discovering a handwritten note threatening a bomb on an airsickness bag.
title: Emergency landing in Mumbai after threat note on Vistara flight
Voter turnout in last phase of Lok Sabha polls inches up to 63.9%

description: Imran Khan calls for studying the Hamoodur Rahman Commission Report to determine the true traitor between General Yahya Khan and Sheikh Mujibur Rahman.
title: Imran posts with ‘fall of Dhaka’ parallels rile army
Deadly shooting leaves one dead and 24 injured in Ohio

description: West Indies stuttered and stumbled before eventually scrambling a five-wicket win over minnows Papua New Guinea in the opening Group C encounter of the T20 World Cup in Guyana on Sunday. Set a modest target of 137, the two-time former champions were undone by clever, disciplined PNG bowling, slumping to 97 for five with only four overs left before all-rounder Roston Chase's unbeaten 42 off 27 balls helped the co-hosts over the line with an over to spare
title: West Indies beat PNG by 5 wickets in T20 World Cup

description: Tragedy struck in Madhya Pradesh's Rajgarh district on Sunday night as a tractor-trolley overturned, resulting in the death of 13 people, including four children. The accident took place in Piplodhijad. Rajgarh Collector Harsh Dikshit informed PTI that the injured had to be rushed to Bhopal due to head and chest injuries.
title: 13 people killed, 15 injured as tractor-trolley overturns in MP

description: Riyan Parag, 22, from Assam enjoyed a breakout IPL season this year with 573 runs at a strike-rate close to 150, coming in at No.4 for the Rajasthan Royals. Playing for Royals since his debut season in 2018, Parag's totals in five previous seasons made for a sorry reading -- 160, 86, 93, 183, 78.
title: Don't even want to watch T20 WC: Riyan Parag
Amul to raise milk price by Rs 2/litre from June 3

description: During the Vitality Blast match against Kent on Sunday, Hampshire Hawks' bowler Chris Wood showcased impeccable sportsmanship, exemplifying true fair play.

description: PTI reported that Bengal governor CV Ananda Bose requested CM Mamata Banerjee to provide a report on post-poll violence in Sandeshkhali for urgent peace restoration.
title: Violence erupts in Sandeshkhali again, Guv seeks report from CM

description: The Maldives will now prohibit Israeli passport holders from entering the country in response to Israel's retaliatory bombardments and ground offensive in Gaza, as reported by Maldives news organization Edition.mv, quoting the President's office. Ali Ihusan said that during a cabinet meeting, President Mohamed Muizzu decided to initiate the necessary legal changes to enforce this ban. A special cabinet committee of ministers has been formed to implement this decision.
title: Maldives moves to ban Israeli citizens from entering country
IMD issues orange alert for Kerala district after heavy rains

description: West Indies captain Rovman Powell won the toss and opted to bowl first against PNG in the opening Group C match. Despite a green-tinged pitch the two-time former champions opted for three spinners - Roston Chase, Akeil Hosein and Gudakesh Motie - in their final 11 at the start of a campaign in which they seek to become the first hosts to lift the T20 World Cup. PNG, who stunned Zimbabwe on an unbeaten run to qualify for their second T20 World Cup appearance, are again reliant on their most experienced players - captain Assad Vala and fellow top-order batters Tony Ura and Lega Siaka - to post a challenging total.
title: Stands empty in Windies' T20 WC opener at home

description: NHAI has increased toll rates by 5% on expressways nationwide from 3.6.2024 based on WPI inflation, affecting 855 user fee plazas on the national highway network.
title: Travelling on national highways set to cost you more from tomorrow

description: Big data professionals see significant salary growth with data warehousing expertise. Java exhibits the narrowest gender gap in data science.

description: Exit polls suggest a BJP-led NDA victory in the 18th Lok Sabha elections, with projections ranging from 342 to 400 seats. Analysts have identified 'Modi stocks' for potential growth under another Modi-led government.

description: India is facing an extreme heatwave, prompting Zomato, an online food delivery platform, to make a special request to its customers.
title: Heatwave in India: Zomato has a request for customers

description: Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump amassed a million followers on TikTok within hours of joining the platform on Sunday. During his presidency, Trump had sought to ban the short video social media platform on national security grounds. By joining TikTok, Trump aims to connect with younger voters in his third bid for the White House.

description: Gautam Gambhir, a former Indian cricketer, expressed his desire to take on the role of coaching the Indian national team on Saturday. His statement comes amidst rumors suggesting he is a leading candidate for the prestigious position.
title: 'I would love to coach the Indian team': Gambhir

description: In the T20 World Cup warm-up against Bangladesh on Saturday, all-rounder Hardik Pandya showed glimpses of his return to form as he fired a solid 23-ball unbeaten 40. He also grabbed a wicket in the game in New York. In IPL 2024, Hardik -- the batter and bowler were disappointing as he scored just 216 runs at a lowly average of 18 and picked up 11 wickets. The 30-year-old has also been reportedly going through tough times in personal life with rumours surrounding his split with wife Natasa Stankovic.

description: In the warm-up game against Bangladesh on Saturday, India batted really well on a tricky track to post 182 for five. While keeper-batter Rishabh Pant fired a 32-ball 53 before retiring, all-rounder Hardik Pandya hit an unbeaten 23-ball 40 to lift India to a solid total. Bowlers then fired in unison to stop Bangladesh at 122 for 9 in their 20 overs.
title: 'Soft ground, spongy pitch' leave Dravid worried
Kejriwal sent to judicial custody till June 5 after surrendering

description: The cricketing community is buzzing with discussions about whether Virat Kohli should open alongside captain Rohit Sharma in the upcoming T20 World Cup. This debate has intensified following Kohli's stellar performance in the IPL 2024, where he topped the charts as the leading run-scorer with 741 runs in 15 innings.

description: The opposition INDIA bloc leaders on Sunday rejected the exit poll results of Lok Sabha elections 2024 as most pollsters gave 350-400 seats to the BJP-led NDA government. The exit polls, released last night, predicted a historic third term for Prime Minister Narendra Modi. Discarding the predictions, the Opposition leaders reiterated that the INDIA bloc will win 295 seats.

description: Former Indian cricketer Gautam Gambhir is being considered as a potential successor to head coach Rahul Dravid in the 2024 T20 World Cup. WV Raman, who previously coached the Indian women's team, has praised Gambhir's strategic acumen and leadership qualities, making him a promising candidate for the Indian cricket team.

description: Captain Rohit Sharma mentioned the Indian squad's uncertainty in finalizing the T20 World Cup batting line-up. Head coach Rahul Dravid highlighted the challenges faced by players due to the spongy pitch in a warm-up match against Bangladesh. At the Nassau County International Cricket Stadium in New York, India defeated Bangladesh by 60 runs, limiting them to 122 for nine after they had amassed 182 for five on Saturday.

description: The exit polls for the 2024 Lok Sabha elections have predicted a resounding victory for the BJP-led NDA, with most polls projecting it to win between 350-400 seats. This is in line with the opinion polls released last month, and far exceeds the expectations of the stock market, which had been pricing in a lower seat count of around 300-320 for the NDA in recent weeks.

description: Yuvraj Singh expressed enthusiasm for cricket's growth in America, highlighting the unique packaging of American sports and the potential for cricket to flourish in the USA. Yuvraj was present at the Fan Park launch at the Oculus Trade Center in New York, where he is an ICC Ambassador for the T20 World Cup.

description: Parents, Pune police, Dr Ajay Taware, Dr Shrihari Halnor, and Atul Ghatkamble were arrested for swapping blood samples in the Pune Porsche crash case. They were remanded to police custody until June 5.

description: Placed in Group A of the T20 World Cup, traditional rivals India and Pakistan will lock horns at the Nassau County International Cricket Stadium in New York on June 9. Pakistan, winners of the 2009 T20 World Cup, have been one of the most consistent teams in the tournament, reaching six semifinals in eight editions. India's only triumph came in 2007.

description: Cricket legend Sunil Gavaskar has endorsed Rishabh Pant as India's starting wicketkeeper for the 2024 T20 World Cup, citing his superior glove work and recent form. Pant's stellar performance in India's warm-up game against Bangladesh, scoring 53 off 32 balls, and his consistent performance in 13 matches, despite a 15-month layoff, have sparked debate.
title: Pant or Samson in starting XI? India legend picks his choice

description: Azam Khan won't be in the ideal frame of mind ahead of his T20 World Cup debut after a series of below-par performances on the England tour, which led to a lot of criticism of the Pakistan wicketkeeper-batsman, especially related to his fitness and heavyset body. Pakistan will play their first match against co-hosts USA in Dallas on June 6.

title: Raveena faces allegations of assault; cops say 'no complaint filed'

description: Cricket fans are focusing on Team India as the T20 World Cup begins, as they haven't won an ICC trophy since 2013. Former Indian cricketer Aakash Chopra predicts it will be challenging to break their ICC trophy drought due to changes in T20 cricket, but notes that the batting order and bowling have remained consistent.

description: Virat Kohli is the centre of attention at the T20 World Cup in the US and the West Indies. Fans are seizing every opportunity to capture the batting legend with their cameras. description: According to exit polls released on Saturday, the BJP-led National Democratic Alliance is projected to secure a significant victory, paving the way for Modi to serve a third consecutive term. The official Lok Sabha election results will be declared on Tuesday.

description: Former India cricketer Sanjay Manjrekar praised Rishabh Pant for his outstanding performance in India's T20 World Cup warm-up game against Bangladesh. Congress's Ajay Maken flags new rule at counting centres

description: Aaron Jones, the USA vice-captain, led his team to a seven-wicket victory over Canada in the 2024 ICC T20 World Cup opener. Despite facing early setbacks, Jones' unbeaten 94 off 40 balls, 10 sixes, and 131-run partnership with Andries Gous helped secure a swift finish, becoming the highest successful chase for the USA in T20Is.

description: On Saturday morning, the Aam Aadmi Party's political affairs committee held a meeting attended by senior members such as Atishi, Raghav Chadha, Durgesh Pathak and Sanjay Singh. A video circulating on social media shows Kohli arriving at the ground in New York, escorted by officials and armed guards.

description: South Korea condemned North Korea for sending 600 balloons filled with trash and excrement, issuing emergency alerts in certain provinces. This came as what Pyongyang calls retaliation for activists flying anti-North Korean leaflets across the border. Earlier also, North Korea sent trash-filled balloons to South. South Korea issued emergency alerts in North Gyeongsang and Gangwon provinces.

description: As Arvind Kejriwal's three-week temporary bail for poll campaigning comes to an end on Sunday, the Delhi chief minister and AAP convenor is set to return to Tihar jail later in the day. Despite this development, the party has assured its top functionaries that Kejriwal will continue to serve as chief minister.

Prior to the elections, the BJP had already secured victory in 10 out of the total 60 seats without opposition. ​​The assembly polls were conducted concurrently with the Lok Sabha elections during the first phase on April 19. Supporters of various political parties gathered near the counting centers across the state, undeterred by the rainy weather conditions.

Despite Dortmund's strong first half, Dani Carvajal and Vinicius Jr. scored in the second half to secure the win. Thibaut Courtois' crucial saves and Carlo Ancelotti's tactical acumen were pivotal in the triumph.
